<TITLE> Nasim leaves for Singapore </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 19 (bdnews24.com) - Former home minister Mohammad Nasim, recently released on bail, flew out of Dhaka Tuesday night to seek medical treatment in Singapore. "Mohammad Nasim left on a Singapore Airlines flight at 11.55pm," said Zia International Airport immigration duty officer-in-charge Asma Siddiqua Milli. Nasim's brother-in-law Sajjad Haider told bdnews24.com: "His younger son Tonmoy Monsur, younger brother Rezaul Karim and younger sister Shirin Akhter are accompanying him." Sajjad said the former home minister will be admitted to Mount Elizabeth Hospital on arrival in Singapore. The ailing Awami League leader was earlier discharged from LabAid Cardiac Hospital, after being freed on bail from police guard Saturday, a hospital spokesperson said. He left the hospital for the airport at around 8.30 pm, hospital spokesperson Mesbah Azad told bdnews24.com. Nasim was arrested on Feb 4, after the promulgation of the state of emergency. A special court on sentenced him to 13 years Oct 8 last year on charges of earning illegal wealth. Nasim was hospitalised on June 24 after suffering a stroke in Kashimpur jail. The High Court granted four months' bail on Aug 6, he was released from police guard at the hospital on Aug 16, after being in detention for 18 months and 11 days. bdnews
